{"TopicId":205670,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Tail fin will not let me dive","CreatedByName":"splashboom","CreatedById":213457,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-20T02:21:10Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"splashboom","CreatedById":213457,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-20T02:21:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe tail fin on my plane lets me take off, but if I want to move it the other way - when I want to dive from altitude - it does nothing. I push the stick all the way and it just stays horizontal. I saw some options to tweak, but nothing that seems to fix this.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI does seem like a safety measure - like to prevent you from lithobraking by accident at take-off. But safety is not the kerbal way!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Hotel26","CreatedById":139095,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-20T03:02:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot a lot to go on.\u00A0 You\u0027ve made a mistake in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022SpacePlane Hangar\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022SpacePlane Hangar\u0022\u003ESPH\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E, though; that much is almost certainly true.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:10px;\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u003Cs\u003E\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 \u003C/s\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAll right, all right!\u00A0 Let\u0027s be constructive.\u00A0 (To get a more detailed answer, you\u0027ll need to supply some more detail about the problem.\u00A0 \u003Cimg alt=\u0022;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Col\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nwhat kind of tail fin is it?\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nwhere is it placed?\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nis it vertically-orientated, horizontally or other?\u00A0 (screenshots are worth 1,000 posts.)\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\ndoes it move at all (e.g. take-off)?\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nwhat are the tweak settings?\u00A0 (screenshot = nice)\u00A0 Authority Limit, Deployment Limit and all the checkbox settings for Pitch, Yaw, Roll...?\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nis it Deployed or not at the time?\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nare you actually using a physical joystick for control input?\u00A0 (rather than e.g. keyboard)\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ol\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-11-20T03:03:23Z\u0022 title=\u002211/20/2021 03:03  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 20, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by Hotel26\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"splashboom","CreatedById":213457,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-20T03:36:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt does move when i want to pitch up. I am using a joystick.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWith the w/s keys it moves both ways (down/up), it is just the joystick that cannot move it down.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022N28bwK6.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002290.00\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/N28bwK6.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-11-20T04:12:57Z\u0022 title=\u002211/20/2021 04:12  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 20, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by splashboom\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003Emore details\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Hotel26","CreatedById":139095,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-20T04:19:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224057409\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022205670\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221637379407\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022213457\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022splashboom\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, splashboom said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt does move when i want to pitch up. I am using a joystick.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nany evidence (i.e. on different craft) that the joystick ever functions in a stick-forward direction?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nalso, if you switch to keyboard, will this craft operate normally?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-11-20T06:15:18Z\u0022 title=\u002211/20/2021 06:15  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 20, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by Hotel26\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"splashboom","CreatedById":213457,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-20T04:30:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI just tried a few other planes, it\u0027s the same situation - joystick does nothing in the forward position. I can use the w key while flying with the joystick, but it gets annoying.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Hotel26","CreatedById":139095,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-20T04:32:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGreat information!\u00A0 This will be a joystick controller binding issue and there is a setup page on it -- but I am very unfamiliar with this area.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSomeone more expert than I will now chime in very shortly and assist you...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cem\u003EBon chance!\u003C/em\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-11-20T04:33:17Z\u0022 title=\u002211/20/2021 04:33  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 20, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by Hotel26\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"splashboom","CreatedById":213457,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-20T04:54:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224057417\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022205670\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221637382770\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022139095\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Hotel26\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n20 minutes ago, Hotel26 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBon chance!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIndeed .. a quick search found this thread. The gist is that it should not work at all (I am on linux!). I have been flying for months until I was bothered enough to look into the dive issue.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u002299196\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed8140668164\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/187031-linux-working-joystick-and-gamepad-models/\u0026amp;tab=comments\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;comment=3647066\u0026amp;embedComment=3647066\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment#comment-3647066\u0022 style=\u0022height:264px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Hotel26","CreatedById":139095,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-20T05:36:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224057426\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022205670\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221637384096\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022213457\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022splashboom\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, splashboom said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI am on linux!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWonderful.\u00A0 Me too, which is probably why I don\u0027t know anything about KSP joystick support.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOnly a palliative, but if you have to use a keyboard, I heartily recommend \u003Cem\u003EAtmospheric Autopilot\u003C/em\u003E as it makes routine keyboard flying much more enjoyable.\u00A0 (I always take-off and land with it disengaged, though.)\u00A0 It offers some remarkable opportunities in the area of cruise climb control.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-11-20T06:14:29Z\u0022 title=\u002211/20/2021 06:14  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 20, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by Hotel26\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"splashboom","CreatedById":213457,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-20T17:31:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is too funny .. The mapping let me assign \u0027Pitch Down\u0027 to forward stick move BUT: it is binary, that is either goes all the way or not at all. Also shows as button 3, which is one of those mysteries. Quite an improvement for flying, but obviously some way to go until normal.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00225FetRfk.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002290.00\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/5FetRfk.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCome to think of it, it is not the first mapping problem I had (and this one seems to have appeared for no reason. Come on Squad what is so hard about mappings? Some things go to some other things \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022213457\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed5100050157\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/204784-joystick-binding-broken/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;comment=4030594\u0026amp;embedComment=4030594\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment#comment-4030594\u0022 style=\u0022height:264px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Hotel26","CreatedById":139095,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-21T03:22:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI took the liberty of building a (stretched) copy (\u0022SplashBoom\u0022):\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022M3Gwwrk.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002290.00\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/M3Gwwrk.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt does 571m/s @ 10.7km although I am still combating heat/dissipation.\u00A0 It lifts off by itself in the 40s and it is able to land/depart water, which is a really nice feature.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCurrent radiator configuration drops performance to 556m/s \u003Cspan\u003E@ 11km, so I think I\u0027m going to have to shoot for a higher cruise altitude.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u003Cs\u003E\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 \u003C/s\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOK, so 558.6 m/s @ 11.6km appears to be sustainable.\u00A0 (If it makes it to Baikerbanur...\u00A0 currently, all heat gauges constant.\u00A0 \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E )\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00220ztKxVM.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.25\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 style=\u0022width:640px;height:auto;\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/0ztKxVM.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-11-21T03:59:32Z\u0022 title=\u002211/21/2021 03:59  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 21, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by Hotel26\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"splashboom","CreatedById":213457,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-21T04:20:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI am quite honored \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E I see that I could probably do with a smaller vertical fin.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Hotel26","CreatedById":139095,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-21T04:35:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have a \u0022soft spot\u0022 for tail-draggers and you\u0027ve made a very attractive airplane -- although Goliaths are always a massive challenge to deal with!\u00A0 Thank you for your inspiration.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Zacspace","CreatedById":188888,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-22T20:27:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224057426\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022205670\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221637384096\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022213457\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022splashboom\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 11/19/2021 at 11:54 PM, splashboom said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI am on linux!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere are dozens of us.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t know if you\u0027re playing on steam but I recently switched to running the windows build under proton. It\u0027s had much better performance for me, as well as actually functional joystick support and the ability to use certain dx11 exclusive mods. It\u0027s not perfect, but the trade between windows version issues and linux version issues has been an easy one to make overall. If you\u0027re able I suggest trying it out.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"splashboom","CreatedById":213457,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-22T21:24:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/188888-zacspace/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022188888\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/188888-zacspace/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Zacspace\u003C/a\u003E, I am playing on steam, and the linux drawbacks have not yet been so overwhelming to make me contemplate switching OS. I heard they are giving another push to proton, so for not I will wait but thanks for the tip!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}